# Caddyfile — HTTPS reverse proxy for PixelOffice (single origin)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WHY: browsers only expose mic/camera (navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia)
# in a SECURE CONTEXT — HTTPS, or localhost. Over http://<lan-ip> it is
# `undefined`, so proximity voice/video calls cannot work. Caddy terminates
# TLS in front of the office so every LAN teammate gets a secure origin.
#
# TOPOLOGY: single origin. Run the Node server with SERVE_CLIENT=true so it
# serves the BUILT client + /api + the Colyseus WebSocket on :2567. The client
# detects it is same-origin (not on Vite's 5173/4173) and dials wss:// on the
# SAME host — see client/src/net/connection.ts. Caddy proxies all of it
# (WebSocket upgrades are handled automatically).
#
# RUN (clean URL on :443, needs sudo on macOS to bind a low port):
#     npm run build                       # build client -> client/dist
#     SERVE_CLIENT=true npm run -w server start   # Node on :2567
#     sudo caddy run --config Caddyfile   # HTTPS in front
#   Teammates open:  https://172.16.1.41
#
# RUN (no sudo, high port):
#     PIXELOFFICE_HOST=172.16.1.41:8443 caddy run --config Caddyfile
#   Teammates open:  https://172.16.1.41:8443
#
# NOTE: `tls internal` uses Caddy's local CA (no public domain needed). The
# FIRST time a teammate opens the URL they'll see a one-time "not private"
# warning — click through ("Proceed"). After that the origin is a secure
# context and calls work. To remove the warning entirely, have teammates trust
# this machine's Caddy root CA (`caddy trust` installs it locally on the host).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Address teammates open. Defaults to this machine's current LAN IP; override
# with the PIXELOFFICE_HOST env var (optionally include a :port).
https://{$PIXELOFFICE_HOST:172.16.1.41} {
	# Local self-signed cert from Caddy's internal CA — no public domain needed.
	tls internal

	# Single backend: the Node server serving client + API + WebSocket.
	reverse_proxy localhost:2567
}
